KPA's Birthday Observed in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 30 (KCNA) -- Seminars, photo exhibitions, lectures and film shows were held in India, Singapore, Equatorial Guinea, Tanzania and South Africa from Apr. 19 to 22 on the occasion of the 74th birthday of the Korean People's Army.
 On display in the venues of the functions were photos showing the Songun leadership exploits of the illustrious commanders of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean films including "70th Birthday of the Heroic Korean People's Army" were screened at the film shows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Juche Philosophy Study Committee of India said in a speech that leader Kim Jong Il developed in depth the Songun idea founded by President Kim Il Sung and that his greatest exploit is that he has trained the KPA into an army strongest in ideology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman stressed that the KPA and the Korean people would always achieve victory only thanks to the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The rector of a Tanzanian school noted that the brilliant history of the KPA is unthinkable without the outstanding leadership of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il.
 The chairman of a branch of the Pretoria City Committee of the African National Congress of South Africa stated that the KPA has developed into an unchallengeable army which has modern offensive and defensive means, invincible armed forces which reliably guarantee peace in the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at a seminar held by the Juche Philosophy Study Committee of India.

Minju Joson Calls for Glorifying Tradition of Korean Working Class 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 30 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson Sunday in an editorial dedicated to May Day, an international holiday of the working class all over the world, stresses the need to glory the proud tradition of the Korean working class which has been boundlessly loyal to the cause of the Workers' Party of Korea and the leaders.
 The Korean working class has successfully fulfilled its mission and duty as an advanced unit of revolution in defending and victoriously advancing the Korean revolution, once arduous and rigorous, the socialist cause of Juche, the editorial says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary spirit and indomitable stamina of the working class fully displayed in the sacred struggle for prosperity of the country and happiness of the people are shining long in the history of the party and the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was thanks to the wise guidance of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il that the Korean working class could greatly contribute to the triumphant advance of the Korean-style socialist cause even under the complicated situation at home and abroad and in manifold difficulties and ordeals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ideological and moral traits and working style of the Korean working class are now on a new higher stage to meet the requirements of the Songun era.
 It is the pride of the Songun era to have a great contingent of the revolutionary working class which regards it as highest honor and pride to uphold the cause of the leader and devotedly serves the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the workers should remain faithful to the revolutionary Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il with their firm revolutionary determination and steadfast will to become Songun revolutionary comrades who share idea and will with him and take the lead in bringing about a great turn for prosperity of socialism.

Functions Held in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 29 (KCNA) -- Meetings, film shows, round-table talks, seminars and book and photo exhibitions were held by the Socialist Party of Romania, the Laos-Korea Youth Friendship Centre, the Laos-Korea Tin Company and the Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism in the period from Apr. 21 to 24 on the occasion of the 74th founding anniversary of the Korean People's Army.
 On display in the venues of the functions were works of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il and photos showing the Songun leadership feats performed by them and introducing the invincible might of the heroic KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the functions referred to the fact that Kim Il Sung laid down the line of building armed forces, guided by the Juche idea, and founded the revolutionary armed forces of the Korean people, the first of their kind in their history, and defeated the U.S. and Japanese imperialists by commanding these forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Supreme Council of the Romanian party said in his speech at a meeting that today the KPA is widely known as the most powerful army in the world, adding that Kim Jong Il's idea of attaching importance to the army and his leadership serve as a source of sure victory of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president of the Mexican committee noted at a seminar that Kim Il Sung's history of leading the army has been given steady continuity by Kim Jong Il, stressing that the KPA which has won victory after victory under the steersmanship of the outstanding brilliant commanders is fully prepared politically and ideologically and in military technique and strikingly demonstrating its might as the main force of the revolution.

Message of Thanks to Kim Yong Nam from Cambodian King
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 29 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, received a message of thanks from Cambodian King Norodom Sihamoni on April 19.
 The king in the message expressed his heartfelt thanks to the president for according him the warmest and cordial hospitality during his state visit to the DPRK from April 17 to 19, 2006. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also extended deep thanks to leading party and state officials of the DPRK and the great Korean people for having warmly welcomed him and his entourage on a state visit to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message expressed firm belief that the long-standing and traditional ties of great friendship and solidarity between the DPRK and Cambodia would grow stronger and develop and contribute to developing the relations of cooperation between the peoples of the two countries.

Patriotic Movement for Great National Unity Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 29 (KCNA) -- The patriotic movement for great national unity is now gaining in scope and strength to be a nationwide movement thanks to the positive support and participation of Koreans from all walks of life. This is a brilliant embodiment of President Kim Il Sung's idea of great national unity. 
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. It goes on:
 This idea is the most just idea of great national unity as it calls on all classes and social strata to place the common wishes and interests of the nation above anything else and unite close irrespective of ideology, ism, political view, religion, property status and social position in order to uphold and achieve national independence. 
 The above-said movement is a national patriotic movement for defending and realizing the national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is based on the Korean nation's unshakable faith and will to struggle to the last for independence and dignity. For this reason the movement is now strengthening the driving force of the nation, increasing the might of national unity while putting a powerful impetus to the overall movement for independent reunification. 
 This movement requires all Koreans to unite close as one for meeting the common wishes and interests of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Patriotism is the ideological basis of the movement. It is the movement that helps heighten the atmosphere of national reconciliation and unity nationwide, reenergize the activities for solidarity and unity being conducted by the organizations of the reunification movement involving people of different circles and increase the role of the "June 15 national joint committee", a nationwide solidarity organization of the reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The movement also helps meet the vicious challenge of the anti-reunification forces with the might of national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S. conservative forces in south Korea are now colluding with each other to usurp power through the next presidential election and bring back the era of confrontation between the north and the south. The above-said movement is strong enough to frustrate the ambition and challenge of the anti-reunification conservative forces.
